AddressInfo.Title: John Lewis Car Park
AddressInfo.AccessComments:
King William Street multi-storey car park reopened on Monday 24 September 2012 following the completion of a major refurbishment project.
The multi-storey car park is now known as the John Lewis car park but remains an Exeter City Council car park and is available to anyone who wishes to use it, not just customers of John Lewis.
The car park now has a pay on foot system, which means that customers pay for their parking when they are ready to leave the car park rather than when they arrive.

GeneralComments: Free to charge, Open charge. No RFID needed. but pay to park from 8am to 6pm 7 days a week. Check for lock up times. Pod-Point T7-S point.
